job_detail_title: Data Scientist - Leading Gov Health Agency
jobAdDetails: Data Scientist - Lading Gov Health AgencyJoin a purpose-driven Analytics team of a leading Government health organisation, that is using data science to support and help deliver programs that change lives.This is a 12 months Day Rate Contract with strong possibility of extension for another 12 months. Candidates must be based in Melb or Brisbane, with hydrid work arrangements - 2-3 days in the office/ rest from home.Australian Citizenship a must.About the TeamThe Analytics, Data & Actuarial (ADA) Division drives insight, forecasting and evaluation to ensure long-term sustainability and impact.Actuarial Insights & Monitoring – providing trusted analysis and advice.Data & Analytics – turning complex data into actionable insights.Scheme Effectiveness & Forecasting – measuring outcomes, evaluating supports, and monitoring financial sustainability.From producing the Annual Financial Sustainability Report to delivering strategic modelling and policy advice, the team plays a pivotal role in shaping evidence-based decision-making and future outcomes.As aData Scientistyou’ll:Work with complex data to deliver reporting, analysis and performance monitoring.Extract, cleanse and prepare data from multiple sources, advising on quality and checks.Apply statistical and predictive modelling, scenario testing and data visualisation to inform decision-making.Contribute to critical reporting for leadership, Ministers and public data sharing.Communicate insights to stakeholders and provide advice on moderately complex enquiries.What we’re looking for:2-3 yearsof relevant analytics or data science experience in gov or other similar agencies with good analytical and data management skills.Hands-on skills and exp inR or Python programming, including data manipulation and analysis.Hands-on experience and skills inSQL / SAS programming.Understanding ofstatistical modelling (GLM, gradient boosting)ormachine learning techniquesa must.Experience in dashboards and visualisations for non-technical stakeholders a big plus.Familiarity with government processes (policy, budget, reporting) a plus.This is your chance to use your technical expertise to influence policy, support national reporting, and contribute directly to outcomes that make a difference for Australians.

You are a high-achieving mathematics/computing graduate, eager to improve human health in partnership with a team of biologists. You are exceptional. You are conscientious, scientifically minded, intelligent and driven.What does the role involve?Our Mission: Meaningfully extend human health span by targeting the root causes of aging.Background:We are focused on genomic damage, which is well suited to analytical approaches including analysis of past data and computational modelling.We are studying the molecular damage that accumulates with age to develop strategies for slowing and reversing it.New high accuracy sequencing techniques are shining a light on these root causes of aging.We have found that to analyse this accumulation of damage, model it, design experiments and analyse the data requires advanced statistics and programming.Unlike many aspects of medicine, the genetic code is highly logical, enabling predictions through modelling.Exposure to the medical sciences is beneficial but not required.Contribute to experimental design and strategy development, using your modelling to guide and shape experiments - not just analysing data from others.You will not be expected to work in the lab and will work in partnership with our lab team.Why work at Systematic Medicine?Work on the most challenging problems. Our mission is harder than going to Mars!Problems that are meaningful.We are focused on meaningfully reducing the burden of disease. Almost all disease burden is age related.Not speeding up a trade by a nano second to squeeze out more money.Secure private funding.Work from our premium office locations in Melbourne. We are based in the new Jumar incubator at the new CSL building and have a non-lab site in a top floor office in Abbotsford.Flexible Hours. You are driven to work hard, but intelligence, mindset and strong adherence to the scientific method is more important. We expect dedicated focused time, but don't require long hours.No travel required. You're welcome to organise conference attendance or go visit other labs.Exceptional pay $120-180k (ex superannuation).What you need to applyCapabilitiesStrong stats, math and problem solving.Strong computer science and statistical coding skills in R and Python at least.ExperienceNot required, but ideally you have 2 years+ full time work experience post academia.EducationUnder grad degree in stats, math, computer science, bioinformatics, molecular biology or similar.Postgraduate studies in the above fields are useful but not required.You need to demonstrate a passion and excitement about our mission.Interview Requirements & TimelinesPlease provide a short cover letter explaining why you would be suitable for the role.The interview process is multi-stage and involved. We will provide you with documents and a question prior to interviews for you to study and ask that you provide a detailed response that will be discussed in the interview. This will require up to a couple of days work.Interviews will begin around the end of September.

We are currently partnering with a well-known Australian organisation that is seeking a Lead Data Scientist to join their established data function. This role, reporting directly to the senior leader across AI, this role will be central in leading a small team of data scientists and executing the organisation’s AI strategy, with a strong focus on advanced ML techniques and large language models (LLMs).This role is a hands-on leadership opportunity where you will combine people leadership with deep technical expertise in designing, developing, and deploying ML, AI, and LLM-based solutions. You will be accountable for embedding best practices, ensuring production readiness, and driving real-world impact from advanced analytics initiatives.What you will be doing…..Lead and mentor a small team of data scientists to deliver innovative AI and ML solutions.Execute the organisation’s AI strategy, with a particular focus on LLM adoption and applied use cases.Design, develop, and deploy ML, AI, and LLM models into production environments.Establish and maintain best practices, frameworks, and standards for scalable AI delivery.Ensure the ethical and responsible use of data and AI in line with organisational policies.Drive model reliability, accuracy, and validation through robust testing and governance.Partner with business and technology stakeholders to maximise adoption, value creation, and impact.Your experience will include……4+ years of experience as a Data Scientist, with recent experience in a leadership or team management role.Proven success in executing AI and data science strategies within complex organisations.Strong expertise in designing, developing, and deploying ML, AI, and LLM-based models into production.Technical depth in Python, R, BI tools, Azure and ML/AI frameworks.Advocate for practical, ethical, and innovative applications of AI and LLMs.Excellent stakeholder engagement and communication skills, with the ability to influence across technical and business teams.To be considered for this role, you must be an Australian Permanent Resident or Australian Citizen.If this position is of interest to you, please click ‘Apply’ or you can just send your details toraed@konnexuscg.com.auKonnexus specialises in the recruitment of permanent and contract professionals within Data Analytics | AI/ML | Data & Platform Engineering. If this role is not right but you want a new position or a conversation about the market, please call us on03 9052 5900and we will pass you onto the right Consultant.

If we feel it's a good fit, we'll be in touch to set up a conversation to get to know you better.

About the RoleThe Data Acquisition Team is the entry point to WEX’s Data-as-a-Service (DaaS) platform responsible for ingesting, validating, and orchestrating raw data from dozens of internal systems and third-party providers.As a Software Engineer, you’ll play a key role in designing and building robust, scalable, and extensible pipelines that feed the entire data ecosystem at WEX. You’ll work across multiple data domains and ingestion patterns—batch, streaming, and event-driven—while ensuring quality, performance, and governance are embedded in every step.WEX is undergoing a data platform transformation—and this team builds the foundation. Every pipeline you create contributes directly to powering analytics, automation, and product intelligence across all business domains.If you’re passionate about scaling data platforms from the ground up, this is your chance to help shape how WEX ingests and leverages its most valuable asset: data.What You’ll DoBuild and maintain high-performance data acquisition pipelines that integrate with a variety of systems across WEX and third-party vendors.Contribute to the development of a modular ingestion platform that enables reusability, reliability, and observability at scale.Implement core pipeline components such as schema validation, transformation orchestration, error handling, and audit logging.Support batch and streaming ingestion flows, ensuring the platform meets varying latency and volume requirements across business units.Ensure traceability, lineage, and security through integration with control plane and governance systems.Participate in code reviews, design sessions, and incident resolution—promoting high standards for code quality and operational reliability.What You Bring4–8 years of experience as a software or data engineer, ideally in high-volume or distributed systems environments.Strong programming skills in Python, Java, Scala, or another systems-focused language.Experience with data integration and ingestion pipelines—you understand what it means to bring data in from source systems, transform it, and deliver it reliably downstream.Solid grasp of engineering fundamentals, including version control, modular design, testing, and performance tuning.Familiarity with concepts like schema evolution, event-driven architectures, observability, and role-based access control.A collaborative mindset—comfortable working across domains, products, and infrastructure layers.A strong sense of ownership and accountability—you care deeply about building systems that last.

Company DescriptionAbout SEEKSEEK’s portfolio of diverse businesses make a positive impact on a truly global scale. Our purpose is to help people live more fulfilling and productive working lives and help organisations succeed. We create world-class technology solutions to connect more people to relevant employment, education, small business and volunteer opportunities. We have a culture of high-performance in our workplaces and celebrate the diversity of our employees who contribute to the success of our organisation.Life at SEEKSEEK’s purpose is at the centre of everything we do.Our SEEK, which defines the way we work, is all about what makes us unique and a little bit different. Passion, Team, Delivery and Future are our principles that drive innovation and creativity. SEEK strives to support employee wellbeing by providing an amazing experience at work which led us to being named AFR BOSS Top 10 Best Places to Work in Technology (2021-2024). We are proud to work in an environment that's inclusive where everyone's unique ideas, experiences and perspectives are valued.Our award-winning head office in Cremorne (just a 4 min walk from Richmond station) provides an exceptional space to collaborate with colleagues. The building provides sweeping views of the city, a games area, sit and stand desks at every workstation, modern end-of-trip facilities and Thursday night drinks which gives our people an opportunity to connect in a social setting.Job DescriptionThe RoleAs a Senior Data Scientist at SEEK, you'll be part of a fast-paced, supportive environment where you can make a real difference. You'll work on complex challenges that have a direct impact on people's lives, helping us evolve our business and reach new heights.You will report a Data Science Lead and work alongside other highly motivated Data Scientists in the Generative AI team. You will collaborate with product managers, designers, engineers, and others across multiple teams to design and develop Generative AI solutions for both internal and external (customer-facing) use cases.Key ResponsibilitiesIn this role, you will be expected to:Research, propose, and implement new AI solutions (and evolve existing ones) to improve a product or business outcome.Compile and develop datasets as appropriate to train or evaluate AI systems.Perform offline evaluation of AI systems and contribute to the design of online experiments.Evangelise appropriate AI methods and explain their benefits and limitations to various audiences, acting as a technical reference within the business on topics related to AI.Break down problems and projects, estimate and prioritise activities, and propose alternatives to overcome obstacles.Work together with Product Managers, Engineers, and other stakeholders to build relationships within the organisation based on trust.Mentor junior Data Scientists and share technical expertise with the DS team.The TeamSituated within the larger Artificial Intelligence & Analytics team at SEEK, the Generative AI team is a practice team focusing on GenAI. The GenAI team has two streams of work. TheApplicationsstream partners with SEEK product owners and may embed Data Scientists into the team to develop and test opportunities to build GenAI-based services. TheCapabilitiesstream builds early-stage prototypes to test the latest GenAI technology, and also develops core functionality into platform capabilities to enable sustainable scaling of GenAI services.We work on a quarterly planning cycle to develop our roadmap, which consists of internal R&D projects as well as partnerships with internal product teams, where we act as specialist consultants. As a Senior Data Scientist, you will work autonomously to deliver one or more initiatives for the team. The team runs various team rituals such as weekly stand-ups and knowledge sharing sessions, monthly team retrospectives, and others as needed. You will also attend project-related meetings as necessary.QualificationsEssential Qualifications, Skills, and ExperienceA MSc or PhD qualification in Computer Science, Data Science, Mathematics, Statistics, or equivalent experience.Professional experience developing and delivering AI/ML solutions.Deep understanding of the theory and practice of how to build, train, evaluate, and optimise AI/ML models.Excellent communication and interpersonal skills, including the ability to communicate complex ideas in simple language.Ability to adapt quickly and thrive in an environment of rapid change.The following are preferred but not essential:Demonstrated experience leading AI/ML projects and managing multiple stakeholders.Deep technical knowledge of the foundations of Generative AI: deep learning; transformers; encoder/decoder models; pre-training and post-training; RLFH; LORA.Hands-on experience training or adapting large language models.Hands-on experience building solutions with pre-trained LLMs, using techniques such as prompt engineering, RAG, agentic workflows, etc.Experience with conversational design and developing conversational AI systems.Additional InformationPermanent PerksAt SEEK we offer:Support of flexible working, including a mix of office and work from home days depending on your role.Paid and unpaid leave benefits including Personal Flexi Days and Volunteer Days, as well as the opportunity to purchase additional leaveSupport for parents with 14 weeks paid primary carers leave and 2 weeks paid leave for partnersSEEKer Support, a confidential service that offers employees up to six sessions with a mental health professional of your choiceTailored career development planning (including Education Assistance Program)At SEEK, we are passionate about fostering a culture of inclusion and wellbeing that embraces and values the diversity of our people. We are a purpose driven business that works with heart.We know teams with diverse ideas, experiences and perspectives are more creative and are critical to ensuring effective delivery and innovating to enable our future success. As such, we welcome applications from people with diverse backgrounds and life experiences, especially as they relate to gender, sexual identity, culture, faith, disability and life stages. If you have the skills, curiosity and an adaptable mindset but don't meet every responsibility or qualification listed in this advertisement, please still get in touch with us.Should you require any specific support or adjustments throughout the recruitment process and beyond, please advise us and we will be happy to assist.For this role, only those candidates with the eligible right to work will be considered.SEEK kindly requests no unsolicited resumes or approaches from recruitment agencies and will not be responsible for any associated fees.
